fragment_downloaded_cb({"url":"Reference-manual_builtin_meson.html#arguments10","fragment":"Arguments\nThe method meson.override_find_program() accepts the following positional arguments:\n\n\n\n\n    \n      \n        Name\n        Type\n        Description\n        Tags\n      \n    \n    \n      \n        progname\n        str\n        \n        \nThe name of the program to override.\n  \n        \n\n  \n  \n      \n      \n        program\n        \nexe | file | program\n\n        \n        \nThe program to set as the override for progname.\n  \n        \n\n  \n  \n      \n      \n        native\n        bool\n        \n        \nIf set to true, the override is for the build machine, and will be returned\nby find_program(..., native : true), otherwise for the host machine. This\nis an important distinction when cross compiling.\n  \n        \n\n  (since 1.12.0)\n  default =\n  false\n  \n  \n      \n    \n  \n"});